The goblins of Sundergrót have set up a secret meeting within the old dwarf ruins.
Sundergrót can be found in the Floodfells.\n\nYou should talk to Agátur outside of Sundergrót.
Talk to Agátur outside of Sundergrót
Rúzat, Agátur, and Náth can be found at Limlók.\n\nYou should talk to the three dwarves.
'[placeholder], something bothers me about the goblins in Sundergrót. I know not what, but something is amiss! Agátur looks as if he has something to say. Spit it out, my friend!'

'I overheard some goblins talking while I was in Sundergrót. At the time, I did not think much of it, but perhaps I should revisit what it was I heard.\n\n'Do you find it odd that the goblins work and camp as if they are commanded, yet there is no commander in sight? Yes, well, I heard a few goblins talking about an important meeting that is soon to happen in Sundergrót. Could this meeting be with this mysterious, absent commander? I say we find this meeting, and learn what is really going on here!'
'Thank you for your assistance on our survey mission. I hope that you will return to Skarháld with us. Please, bring us word from Grimbeorn as soon as you hear something.'
'It is always a pleasure to receive assistance from the great [placeholder]. I hope our paths cross once more, my friend!'
'Aye, it looks like my curiosity was warranted. I am glad that we stopped those goblins from joining forces with Gundabad.'
'I am glad that we stopped those Goblins from joining forces with Gundabad.'
